Interview Explanation
"Diameter through any node equals the height of its left subtree plus the height of its right subtree. While performing a postorder DFS to calculate heights, 
I update a global answer with leftHeight + rightHeight at every node. Since each node is visited once and height information is reused immediately, the overall 
complexity becomes O(N) with O(H) recursion stack space."
